@node "Extensions" "Extensions"
@{u}File extensions@{uu}

@{b}.PFA@{ub} Printer Font Ascii Adobe type 1 shape of font in hex format ie like the one inserted into the postscript file if the font data is included in file.

@{b}.PFB@{ub} Printer Font Binary This is the actual shape of the font, it doesn't have to have the extension to work.

@{b}.AFM@{ub} Adobe font metric contains graphic spacing data for printing. This is required on amigas and some IBM applications, others and mac computers use pfm files instead.

@{b}.PFM@{ub} Printer font metric file alternative method of graphic spacing.

@{b}.PPD@{ub} printer font download file for applemac computers.

@endnode
